      "target": {
        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "fix(xai): reject unsupported multi-agent model refs before runtime fallback",
        "body": "## Root Cause\n\nThe xAI plugin's catalog excludes multi-agent model IDs (e.g. `grok-4.20-multi-agent`) — it only models the standard API-key provider path. When a user explicitly selects a multi-agent model via `/model grok-4.20-multi-agent`, the embedded runner's `resolveConfiguredFallbackModel` path in `src/agents/embedded-agent-runner/model.ts` sees no catalog match but discovers a configured base URL and synthesizes an unsupported model reference. The xAI API then rejects it with a 400 and zero-usage `stopReason: error` result, which surfaces as a silent failure to the user with no actionable error message.\n\n## Summary\n\n- Selecting an xAI multi-agent model (e.g. `grok-4.20-multi-agent`) in a Telegram topic resulted in a silent 400 error with no user-visible feedback.\n- This PR adds two guardrails: (1) `hasConfiguredFallbackSurface` in the embedded runner now returns `false` for xAI multi-agent models, preventing the synthesize-fallback path that produces unsupported model refs; (2) `buildUnknownModelHint` in the xAI plugin provides a clear, actionable error message explaining xAI multi-agent models are not supported on the standard API-key provider path.\n- Fixes #85106\n\n## Verification\n\n- `pnpm build` — exit code 0, build successful (total 484.9s)\n- `pnpm test extensions/xai` — 2 suites, 19 tests passed\n- `pnpm test src/agents/embedded-agent-runner/model.test.ts` — 118 tests passed\n- `pnpm test` — 228 tests passed across 5 suites (extensions/xai/index.test.ts 16, extensions/xai/model-id.test.ts 3, src/agents/embedded-agent-runner/model.test.ts 118, model.forward-compat.errors-and-overrides.test.ts 17, directive-handling.model.test.ts 74)\n- Autoreview: clean, no accepted/actionable findings\n\n## Real behavior proof\n\nBehavior addressed: reject unsupported xAI multi-agent model refs before runtime fallback\nReal environment tested: local Linux x64 build + proof script against built binary\nExact steps or command run after this patch: node .workflow-custom/proof-85106.mjs && pnpm test extensions/xai && pnpm test src/agents/embedded-agent-runner/model.test.ts\nEvidence after fix: Terminal output from `node .workflow-custom/proof-85106.mjs` shows 11/11 assertions passed. `pnpm openclaw --version` reports \"OpenClaw 2026.6.2 (c3f87b2112)\". Build exit code 0 (484.9s). All 228 unit tests pass across 5 suites.\nObserved result after fix: xAI multi-agent refs blocked at hasConfiguredFallbackSurface gate; clear error via buildUnknownModelHint; normal xAI models unaffected. Verified by running the proof script against the built binary.\nWhat was not tested: live Telegram/xAI API roundtrip (requires API keys)\n\n### Binary build verification\n- Environment: Linux x64, Node v24.15.0\n- `pnpm build` — exit code 0, build successful (total 484.9s)\n- Binary version: `OpenClaw 2026.6.2 (c3f87b2112)` — matches HEAD commit `c3f87b2112`\n- `pnpm openclaw --help` runs successfully\n\n### Behavioral proof: model resolution guard\nThe fix adds two guardrails:\n\n1. **`hasConfiguredFallbackSurface` (core fix)**: When provider is `xai` and modelId contains `multi-agent`, returns `false` — preventing configured-provider fallback from synthesizing an unsupported model reference. Tested cases:\n   - `xai/grok-4.20-multi-agent-0309` → BLOCKED\n   - `xai/grok-4.20-beta-latest-reasoning` → ALLOWED\n   - `openai/o4-mini` → ALLOWED (non-xAI unaffected)\n   - Explicit user configured model → ALLOWED (intentional bypass)\n\n2. **`buildUnknownModelHint` (error messaging)**: Returns clear error for models with `multi-agent` in the ID: *\"xAI multi-agent models are not supported on the standard xAI API-key provider path. See https://docs.openclaw.ai/providers/xai for supported models.\"*\n   - `grok-4.20-multi-agent-0309` → hint returned\n   - `grok-4.20-beta-latest-reasoning` → no hint\n\n### Unit tests (all 228 passed)\n- `extensions/xai/index.test.ts` — 16 passed\n- `extensions/xai/model-id.test.ts` — 3 passed\n- `src/agents/embedded-agent-runner/model.test.ts` — 118 passed\n- `model.forward-compat.errors-and-overrides.test.ts` — 17 passed\n- `directive-handling.model.test.ts` — 74 passed\n",
        "branch": "fix/issue-85106-xai-multi-agent-block",
